Parliament, Thursday, 28 November 2019 – The Standing and Select Committees on Appropriation will hold a public hearing on Friday, 29 November 2019, on the 2019 Adjustments Appropriation Bill [B 16-2019] and the 2019 Medium Term Budget Policy Statement. The objective of the Bill is to effect adjustments to the appropriation of money from the National Revenue Fund for the requirements of the state with respect to the 2019/20 financial year and to provide for matters incidental thereto. Details of the meeting are as follows: Date: Friday, 29 November 2019
	Time: 09:00 am 
	Venue: Committee Room M514, Fifth Floor, Marks Building. ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSONS OF THE STANDING AND SELECT COMMITTEES ON APPROPRIATIONS, MR SFISO BUTHELEZI AND MS DIKELEDI MAHLANGU. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairpersons, please contact: Name: Felicia Lombard
	Parliamentary Communication Services
	Tel: 021 403 8285
	Cell: 081 548 7011
